<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<style>
    body {
        margin: auto;
        width: 50%;
        padding: 10px;
    }
    h1 {
        text-align: center;
    }
    blockquote {
        background: rgb(245, 245, 245);
        border-left: 5px solid rgb(204, 203, 255);
        margin: 1.5em 0.5em;
        padding: 3px 20px 3px;
        display: flex;
    }
</style>
<head>
    <title>URL Shortner</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to URL Shortner</h1>
    <p>This service create and provide custom short aliases redirecting to long URLs. Too tracking number of clicks, date and time.</p>
    <p>For example, if we shorten this link:<p>
    <blockquote>
        <p>
            <a href="https://github.com/francieleportugal/url-shortner">https://github.com/francieleportugal/url-shortner</a>
        </p>
    </blockquote>
    <p>to custom name <i>urlshortner</i>, we would get:<p>
    <blockquote>
        <p>{nameDomain}/urlshortner</p>
    </blockquote>
</body>
</html>